      • discard

        public void discard()
        Description copied from interface: Probe
        This method discards and performs cleanup on this probe.

        After calling this method, this probe is not usable anymore in the sense that no value change notifications are thrown, and any call to Probe.getValue() will throw an exception.
        If you want to use the probe again you need to call Probe.setup(Probed) on the probe.

        Specified by:
        discard in interface Probe<ValueType>
        Overrides:
        discard in class ProbeImpl<ValueType>
        See Also:
        Probe.isDiscarded()
